    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName>, <date>Sept. 1st 5617</date></p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Cohen</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">By the present opportunity I<lb/> send you one set prayer books
                such<lb/> as you ordered, and I hope they<lb/> will be in time for your niece at<lb/>
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>. They came from the<lb/> Bindery today. I take the
                liberty to<lb/> enclose six Daily Prayers which<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Carvalho</persName> requested me to forward<lb/> as they may be needed
                with you. Have<lb/> the goodness to inform him that <add>?</add><lb/> are in your
                possession. I hope to see<lb/> you next week; but I should be pleased<lb/> if you
                would be first with us on <date>Thursday</date><lb/> evening at the dedication of
                our place<lb/> of worship. I am much hurried about<lb/> the preparations. Give my
                respects to all.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">I. Leeser</persName>.</p>
            <p><addressee>J. S. Cohen, Jr., Esq.</addressee><lb/>
                <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
